Paris-Saclay Universit=C3=A9 opens a Tenure track position in Machine=20
Learning for Scientific Modelling. The candidate is integrated in the=20
Machine Learning and Optimization AO/TAU team of the LISN (CNRS UMR=20
9015, INRIA), their teaching duty will take place in the AI Master in=20
Paris-Saclay.

Their research project will participate into machine learning accounting=20
for existing models (laws, ordinary differential equations, invariances,=20
simulators) in scientific domains.

Some expertise in the following (non exhaustive list) will be appreciated=
:
* graph neural networks, (approximate) message propagation;
* generative models; modeling/interpretation of latent structures;=20
integration of constraints in neural architectures (invariance, dynamics)=
;
* transfer learning (domain adaptation, optimal transport;=20
multi-fidelity models).


